# Git Commit Message Rules

## Rule: Maximum 10 Words
All commit messages must be **10 words or less**.

### Examples:
✅ Good:
- "Add user authentication"
- "Fix login bug"
- "Update dependencies"
- "Cleanup: enhance .gitignore and add .gitkeep files"

❌ Bad:
- "Add user authentication with JWT tokens and refresh token support" (13 words)
- "Fix the login bug that was causing users to be unable to log in" (12 words)

### Format:
- Use imperative mood (Add, Fix, Update, Remove)
- Be concise and descriptive
- Use prefixes when helpful: "Fix:", "Add:", "Update:", "Remove:", "Cleanup:"

